column2: Title: Documentary photograph of children holding an MWRO banner outside a Public Welfare office on Howkins Street during a demonstration.
column3: Abstract: This black and white photograph depicts a demonstration outside a Public Welfare office on Howkins Street.  An 8-year-old girl holds a Mothers Welfare Rights Organization (MWRO) flag, while a younger child stands beside her holding flyers.  Another small child stands behind them on the steps of the building. The composition focuses on the children and the MWRO flag in the foreground, with the Public Welfare office sign and building entrance in the background.
